http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Missing-boy-found-dead/article14006418.ece

The missing of Basava Sai Teja (6) turned tragic with the locals finding his body in a drain in the Kothapet police station limits on Monday. He was a resident of Kasipathi Veedhi near Cholera Hospital.The boy was missing from January 14, and the police registered a case on January 16. The decomposed body of Teja was found in outfall drainage at K.L. Rao Nagar.Teja, who left home on Bogi festival, did not return. Police are trying to find out whether the boy accidentally slipped into the drain while playing or killed by some miscreants for any reason.